df_dict = pd.read_excel('Data/Seguimiento.xlsx', sheet_name = None)
df = pd.DataFrame()
In [ ]: 
for i, sheet in enumerate(df_dict):
    if sheet == 'Hoja75': continue # Last sheet is empty

    del df_dict[sheet]['Genotipo'] # Coded in Genocode
    del df_dict[sheet]['Nº Registro'] # Id no needed
    del df_dict[sheet]['Nº DNA'] # Id no needed
    del df_dict[sheet]['Fecha Nacimiento'] # Info obtained from other columns
    del df_dict[sheet]['Fecha  Inicio Tratamiento'] # Info obtained from other columns
    del df_dict[sheet]['Edad  RM Control'] # Info obtained from other columns
    del df_dict[sheet]['Fecha RM Control'] # Info obtained from other columns
    del df_dict[sheet]['SCORE TOTAL'] # Repeated
    del df_dict[sheet]['Tratamiento'] # Coded in Genocode Tratamiento.1
    del df_dict[sheet]['IgG'] # Too Many NaN
    del df_dict[sheet]['IgA'] # Too Many NaN
    del df_dict[sheet]['Ferritina'] # Too Many NaN
    del df_dict[sheet]['DMO'] # Too Many NaN
    del df_dict[sheet]['Z-Score'] # Too Many NaN
    del df_dict[sheet]['T-Score'] # Too Many NaN
    
    with warnings.catch_warnings(record=True): # Disable append deprecation warnings
        df = df.append(df_dict[sheet].assign(id=i)) # Ad patient id and combine tables

df.insert(0, 'id', df.pop('id'))
df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

KNeighbours ¶

In [ ]: 
# Create 10 models with different neighbours attribute
KNeighbours_models = [KNeighborsClassifier(metric='minkowski', n_neighbors=i) for i in range(1,30)]
for m in KNeighbours_models: m.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Build a dataframe with the results
acc_col=[]
neighbors_col = range(1,30)
for m in KNeighbours_models: acc_col.append(100.0 * m.score(X_test, y_test))
KNeighbours_comparison = {'Accuracy':acc_col, 'Neighbours':neighbors_col}
KNeighbours_comparison = pd.DataFrame(KNeighbours_comparison)

SVC ¶

In [ ]: 
kernels = ['linear', 'rbf', 'sigmoid']
svc_models = [SVC(kernel=k) for k in kernels]

for i in range(1,6): 
    svc_models.append(SVC(kernel='poly', degree=i))
    kernels.append(f'poly_{i}')

for m in svc_models: m.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Build a dataframe with the results
acc_col=[]
for m in svc_models: acc_col.append(100.0 * m.score(X_test, y_test))
svc_comparison = {'Accuracy':acc_col, 'Kernel':kernels}
svc_comparison = pd.DataFrame(svc_comparison)
